How can I write in LaTeX the fraction 1/21

To write a fraction like 1/21 in LaTeX, you can use the `\frac` command provided by the `amsmath` package (which is usually loaded by default).

Here's how you can do it:

`\frac{1}{21}`

This will produce the desired output: $\frac{1}{21}$.

Note that you don't need to add any space or punctuation around the `\frac` command. It will automatically format the fraction for you.

If you want to customize the appearance of the fraction, such as changing the font size or style, you can wrap the `\frac` command inside other LaTeX commands. For example:

`\text{\small $\frac{1}{21}$}`

This would produce a smaller-sized fraction: $\frac{1}{21}$.
